  "prompt": "Why Arnab Goswami resign times now? And start entrepreneurs.?",
  "response": "Arnab Goswami resigned from Times Now in November 2016. His departure was reportedly motivated by a desire to pursue independent journalism and create a new media venture that he could lead with his own vision and editorial direction. This led to the founding of Republic TV, a news channel he co-founded with Rajeev Chandrasekhar and ARG Outlier Media. \n\nGoswami's decision to leave Times Now was influenced by his ambition to build a media outlet that could operate with greater editorial freedom and flexibility, which he felt was not fully possible under the constraints of a larger media conglomerate. Republic TV launched in May 2017 and quickly became one of the prominent news channels in India, continuing Arnab Goswami's style of outspoken and aggressive journalism.",
